-- Insurer Beazley's first half boosted by investment returns
-- By Richa Naidu in Bangalore
-- Tue Jul 22, 2014 02:26AM EDT
-- None



July 22 (Reuters) - Lloyd's of London insurer Beazley Plc <BEZG.L> posted a 61 percent rise in first-half profit, thanks to a surge in  investment income and a drop in catastrophe payouts.

Beazley, which writes marine, casualty and property cover, reported a pretax profit of $132.9 million for the first-half ended June 30, up from $82.3 million a year earlier. [ID:nRSV9262Ma]